Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.84,0:00:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One year ago, in East Okuho Village...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.64,0:00:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I, Kudou Shinichi, solved a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.31,0:00:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A letter that said I'd made a mistake in my reasoning...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.27,0:00:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had been sent to me by way of Hattori Heiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.02,0:00:17.02,Character Card,,0,0,0,,\hOkuda Makato (19)\h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.65,0:00:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to meet the sender, Okuda Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.44,0:00:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went to visit East Okuho Village, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.65,0:00:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s whereabouts were currently unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.49,0:00:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, for some reason, it seemed the people of the village...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.29,0:00:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Harbored a sense of hatred towards Kudou Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.83,0:00:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went alone to the mountain cabin where\NMakoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had arranged to meet me - however...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.92,0:00:36.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.47,0:00:41.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.22,0:00:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.47,0:00:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I created it to secretly test on Kudou kun\Nthe next time he came to stay over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.10,0:00:51.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A miracle cure that would restore his body,\Ntransformed into that of a child by Apotoxin 4869...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.81,0:00:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back to that of a high-school student!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.61,0:00:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.61,0:00:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.03,0:01:02.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shinichi"?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.86,0:01:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.20,0:01:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.99,0:01:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lost his memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.62,0:01:12.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That drug is just a prototype.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.71,0:01:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though there may be a slight calculation\Nerror, the range of its effectiveness...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.29,0:01:17.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will be 24 hours at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.34,0:01:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,24 hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.88,0:01:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't regain his memory before then, that'll be bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.51,0:01:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, shouldn't we take Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} along to the crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.35,0:01:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That might help him remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.31,0:01:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This person, Kudou Shinichi, deduced that it was a\Nforced double suicide instigated by Mayor Hinohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.98,0:01:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was the mistake in Kudou's deduction?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.48,0:01:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive behind Mayor Hinohara's forced double suicide was...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.95,0:01:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The desperation he felt after his doctor diagnosed him with cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.37,0:01:54.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's what Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said a year ago,\Nbut the real situation poses a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.88,0:01:54.37,CharCard2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(210,0)}Kawauchi Misato (36)\N{\fs13}\h\hNewspaper Reporter\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.87,0:01:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was cancer, but the tumor was benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.67,0:02:01.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mayor had been pleased to hear it\Ncould be completely cured through surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.63,0:02:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.22,0:02:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kudou, what does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.76,0:02:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know all about it, Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.89,0:02:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About your ulterior motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.52,0:02:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the truth that must not be said.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.15,0:02:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.98,0:02:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.19,0:02:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.95,0:02:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as I find the real criminal,\Nyou can get out, but you need to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.33,0:02:35.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I definitely have to settle this case before night falls without fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.65,0:02:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An impossible crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.08,0:02:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A baffling murder trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.82,0:02:41.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.65,0:02:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.50,0:02:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were Shinichi, I'm sure he'd...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.26,0:02:49.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}! Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I beg you, please restore Shinichi to the way he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.95,0:03:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.84,0:03:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A desperate crisis...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A splendid revival reverses the conclusion to a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.60,0:03:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As Heiji discloses the astounding truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.39,0:03:19.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran can't stop crying for Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.31,0:03:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.81,0:03:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.66,0:03:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.78,0:05:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Ran, could you head home before me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.91,0:05:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.16,0:05:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll catch up with you right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.46,0:05:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.30,0:05:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.48,0:05:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.60,0:05:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi's leaving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.50,0:05:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! Don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.68,0:05:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,SHINICHI!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.41,0:06:03.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.96,0:06:07.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I found the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} in the forest and ran after him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.96,0:06:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I lost my footing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.84,0:06:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? My wounds have been dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.35,0:06:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who on earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've found Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.90,0:06:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.07,0:06:35.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.57,0:06:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with these bandages?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.95,0:06:42.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I fell down in the forest and lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like someone carried me here and treated my injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.62,0:06:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet it must have been the owner of this cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.33,0:06:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to give them our thanks when they return.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.59,0:06:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it looks like the owner of this cabin isn't a good person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:06:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A transceiver?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.80,0:07:01.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.76,0:07:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the room next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come and look. It's quite impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.39,0:07:09.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come over there? But the door's been boarded up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.85,0:07:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can go back outside and come in through the window, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.23,0:07:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I guess we could.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.74,0:07:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.99,0:07:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.16,0:07:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's completely covered with pictures and articles of that detective kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it seems they've really taken a fancy to that "Kudou" guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.04,0:07:33.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the point of wanting to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.59,0:07:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His photo's been chopped to shreds!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.38,0:07:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.13,0:07:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you didn't see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.76,0:07:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who carried you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.76,0:07:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.97,0:07:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did see the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} in the forest, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.72,0:07:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:07:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.02,0:07:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears that the owner of this cabin is\Nnone other than the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.69,0:07:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A white hair from a wig made of polyester.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:08:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} you met had white hair, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.95,0:08:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but he didn't seem to be that bad of a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.33,0:08:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was scary, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.66,0:08:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.00,0:08:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he was the one who gave Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} medical treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.54,0:08:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he was being kind in order to lower your guard,\Nso that he could do bad things to you afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:17.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.80,0:08:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One thing's for certain, he's a dangerous guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.39,0:08:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An empty box of bullets for a handgun...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.05,0:08:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the scattered remains of mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.64,0:08:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five or six of them have been smashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.60,0:08:32.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the real clincher is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.69,0:08:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The nasty words carved into this table.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.15,0:08:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Failure means death."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.53,0:08:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.74,0:08:44.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there's an empty box of bullets...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.66,0:08:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.45,0:08:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like the Shiragami sama is walking\Naround with a dangerous object in his possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.08,0:08:50.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.79,0:08:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady newspaper reporter...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.71,0:08:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it looked like she'd been stabbed by Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that have been the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.96,0:08:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.50,0:09:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he has a grudge against Kudou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.61,0:09:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.89,0:09:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that were the case, he must have called Kudou and\Nthe woman over to that house and ambushed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.81,0:09:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did the culprit not leave any footprints near the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.73,0:09:17.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ground was even muddy from the rain during the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.27,0:09:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could he have been lying in wait inside\Nthe house prior to it starting to rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.11,0:09:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.45,0:09:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if that were so, he couldn't have left\Nthe house without leaving footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.03,0:09:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of the case that happened there a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.95,0:09:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I decided to check around the house last night, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.83,0:09:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be impossible to get into or out of the\Nhouse without stepping on the ground somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.92,0:09:42.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, this morning, before\Nthe ambulance and the police arrived...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.97,0:09:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I looked around inside the house just in case...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.47,0:09:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there was nobody there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.05,0:09:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.18,0:09:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.60,0:09:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ambulance and the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.77,0:09:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who called them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.48,0:09:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.85,0:09:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.94,0:09:58.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the same both times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.90,0:10:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said it was a young man with an awfully hoarse voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:02.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.82,0:10:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that mean it was Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.90,0:10:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.03,0:10:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The call to the inn where the newspaper reporter,\NKawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was staying was just the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.79,0:10:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A young man with a rough voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.04,0:10:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The people there told me that he said he was Kudou Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.42,0:10:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean Kudou was the one who called out that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.71,0:10:22.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also called the ambulance and the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.97,0:10:30.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe that guy faked his memory loss and was planning something...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.22,0:10:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said something like that as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.47,0:10:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.56,0:10:37.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one thing she said last night that bothered me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.48,0:10:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, what's with that face?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.11,0:10:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you think I hadn't found you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.69,0:10:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, when I went to the inn where she\Nwas staying to ask her about it, she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.32,0:10:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s memory loss is fake."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.45,0:10:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"He's definitely up to something."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.50,0:10:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.91,0:10:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What that woman said last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.38,0:11:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was she just trying to trick him into revealing himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.09,0:11:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.17,0:11:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can be sure that the owner of this house is someone dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.80,0:11:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have the police come here immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.38,0:11:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.09,0:11:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I can find the way out of the forest, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.14,0:11:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for finding my way back here again...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.85,0:11:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what if we get the bonfire going again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.77,0:11:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can use the smoke as a landmark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.52,0:11:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bonfire?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:22.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.32,0:11:25.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next to that rock that looks like a tombstone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.86,0:11:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those ashes are from a bonfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was burning from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.86,0:11:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have been planning to eat dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.16,0:11:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when we came here, he got scared and ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.87,0:11:41.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think he might have escaped through\Nthe small window in the room next door?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.46,0:11:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that window?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.34,0:11:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, wouldn't that be too small for an adult to escape through?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.20,0:11:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child's footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.97,0:11:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Kudou.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:12:00.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They might have used that letter to call\Nhim here so they could lock him in...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.75,0:12:04.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, he escaped through that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.00,0:12:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who could have locked him in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.90,0:12:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who sent the letter, Okuda Makoto,\Nhas been missing for the last half year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.99,0:12:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto has probably been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.07,0:12:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could Okuda Makoto still be alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.00,0:12:22.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, wait a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I need to think this through again from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That photo of Kudou that's been chopped to shreds...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.82,0:12:31.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the culprit has a big-time grudge against Kudou.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.30,0:12:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the words on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.17,0:12:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would the culprit be doing that would risk his life?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.75,0:12:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Revenge on Kudou?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.99,0:12:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The empty box of bullet in the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.00,0:12:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely the culprit has a handgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.30,0:12:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though they must have had plenty of chances to shoot Kudou...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.50,0:12:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why haven't they done it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.22,0:12:56.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They used a kitchen knife when they stabbed that old lady, Kawauchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.82,0:12:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't they want to use the gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.11,0:13:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the one other thing that's bothering me is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.45,0:13:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mirrors that have been shattered to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.50,0:13:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did they need to break them into so many pieces like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.81,0:13:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.68,0:13:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.52,0:13:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, while you're off calling for the police, there's\Na little something I want you to check for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.61,0:13:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how can I check something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.16,0:13:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.83,0:13:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can find it just fine using this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.92,0:13:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.92,0:13:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, the smoke can be seen even from a distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.05,0:13:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He won't get lost spinning in circles in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.92,0:13:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of spinning in circles, what do you think it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.64,0:13:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sport that Mayor Hinohara played?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.51,0:14:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was a track and field event.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.93,0:14:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember when I told you that we asked the people\Nat the inn about the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.36,0:14:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the same time, we asked them what\Nevent Mayor Hinohara competed in, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.32,0:14:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said they didn't remember the name,\Nbut it was one where you spin around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.07,0:14:18.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Spin around?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.45,0:14:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A track-and-field event where you spin around in circles?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.99,0:14:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be the hammer throw or the discus or something, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.37,0:14:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, they said he was good at the ring toss too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.46,0:14:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ring toss?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.75,0:14:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Mayor Hinohara's son, Daiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},\Nwould brag about it to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.92,0:14:38.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd say his father was really good at the ring toss,\Nand he always got a perfect score of 100 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.14,0:14:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said 100 points?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.23,0:14:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that the policeman's voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.94,0:14:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.53,0:14:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:15:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened? What's wrong? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.16,0:15:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.25,0:15:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.08,0:15:09.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I saw him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.88,0:15:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden I lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.43,0:15:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.18,0:15:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your gun holster is open!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.06,0:15:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They didn't take the pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.69,0:15:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why the gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.57,0:15:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he only bought the bullets but hadn't acquired a gun yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.82,0:15:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.90,0:15:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still haven't figured that guy out yet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.41,0:15:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've more-or-less figured out the rest of the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.45,0:15:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's forget the cabin for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.87,0:15:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we gather everyone together at Mayor\NHinohara's house and solve the mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.96,0:15:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A high-school detective from Osaka? Hattori Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.47,0:16:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying that detective will explain to us police...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.64,0:16:08.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth behind the incident where\NKawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was stabbed here this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.77,0:16:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's it exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.69,0:16:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.61,0:16:23.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're ready to do so, I'd like you to bring forth the person whose\Nunidentified footprints left with yours through the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I brought him along...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.74,0:16:27.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner of those footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.88,0:16:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why does he have blood on his clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.46,0:16:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.59,0:16:40.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not going to tell me that Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.17,0:16:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Among the footprints that were left in front of this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.43,0:16:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you exclude the footprints of those who were at the inn and\Nhave an alibi, as well as the stabbing victim, Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.56,0:16:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that remains...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.27,0:16:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are this guy's footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.35,0:16:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's blood is on his clothes and his\Nfingerprints are on the murder weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.61,0:16:58.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how you look at it, he has to be the culprit, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.03,0:17:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.74,0:17:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy is the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.75,0:17:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.21,0:17:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean there was no trick used in this crime at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.58,0:17:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.34,0:17:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.85,0:17:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some kind of tactic?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.43,0:17:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no tactic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.85,0:17:32.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, this guy called Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} over here on the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.06,0:17:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this guy was the one who stabbed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.48,0:17:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.90,0:17:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it just this morning that you were so insistent about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.32,0:17:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said this guy would never stab anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.91,0:17:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.28,0:17:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That newspaper reporter...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.08,0:17:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she'd expose the error I made a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.21,0:17:59.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the prestige and pride I'd built up to this point...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.09,0:18:02.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She threatened to rip it all to shreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.93,0:18:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I really didn't understand exactly what she meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.89,0:18:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was scared, scared. And without thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.30,0:18:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.43,0:18:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all wrong. He's not Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.70,0:18:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shinichi that I've waited for...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.57,0:18:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who fills my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.37,0:18:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the Shinichi I've been longing for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.18,0:18:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, it's just like Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.89,0:18:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My tears...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.27,0:18:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My tears just won't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.45,0:19:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you actually saying you called that newspaper\Nreporter, Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, here and stabbed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.79,0:19:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. There's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.21,0:19:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My God, I can hardly believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.79,0:19:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your deduction a year ago was magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.17,0:19:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw through the trick in an instant...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.01,0:19:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And showed us how to settle the case as fast as lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.35,0:19:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could you have done something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.18,0:19:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've overestimated me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.31,0:19:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not a god. I can hate people, and I can make mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.07,0:19:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like in that case a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.78,0:19:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I called Mayor Hinohara a criminal\Neven though he hadn't committed a crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, it seems you've lost your\Nmemory and can't remember it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.41,0:20:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for that incident, we have concrete proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.62,0:20:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.46,0:20:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The results of the analysis have arrived,\Nso I've come to inform you just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.38,0:20:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Analysis?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.59,0:20:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one that boy from Osaka ask me to have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.68,0:20:18.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To see if the knife that was the murder weapon and\Nthe bits of chain inside the charm the boy had...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.64,0:20:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Matched or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.69,0:20:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And? How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.40,0:20:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like you said, they didn't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.15,0:20:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great! It's just like I deduced!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.11,0:20:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Charm? You mean that charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.87,0:20:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could that be connected with the knife?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.95,0:20:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it that you said didn't match?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.67,0:20:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was something that we are all born with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.13,0:20:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bequeathed to us by heaven above.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.13,0:20:49.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An emblem that never changes throughout our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.76,0:20:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in a criminal investigation, because everyone's are different...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.10,0:21:01.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're a mark that provides an extremely\Ndependable and high degree of proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.35,0:21:05.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fingerprints, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.73,0:21:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.77,0:21:08.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.15,0:21:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.07,0:21:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.07,0:21:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.79,0:21:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.00,0:21:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.38,0:21:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.26,0:21:38.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time for the curtain to close on this costume ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.60,0:21:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Costume ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.31,0:21:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.10,0:21:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, if we want to call it that, the trick in this case would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.27,0:21:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.44,0:21:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really now, how could anyone think the high-school\Ndetective, Kudou Shinichi, would ever stab someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.78,0:21:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first thing I noticed was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.53,0:22:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The behavior of that girl there - old man Mouri's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.29,0:22:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though Kudou, who she has waited so long for, had\Nappeared, why was she being so cold and distant to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.42,0:22:13.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally she'd stick to him and not let go -\Nand all the more so if he'd lost his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.63,0:22:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the start, I thought she was just trying\Nto hide her embarrassment, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.39,0:22:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I was investigating the culprit's cabin in the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.43,0:22:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured out the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.23,0:22:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit's cabin?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.85,0:22:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the place with chopped up pictures of Kudou affixed to the wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.90,0:22:35.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And where mirrors had been smashed into\Nlittle pieces and scattered on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.82,0:22:43.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guy chopped up the photos because he hates Kudou, but as for the\Nmirrors, there's only one reason for them to be smashed to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.37,0:22:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was something he couldn't stand at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.50,0:22:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His face, Kudou's face, reflected in those mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.30,0:22:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.42,0:22:58.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, he's had plastic surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.68,0:23:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To become this great detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.73,0:23:10.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To have this stupid high-school student's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.66,0:23:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, they're...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.62,0:23:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Identical!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.34,0:23:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s face?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.21,0:23:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He requested that I come to that cabin and locked me in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.26,0:23:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think probably so that he could pretend\Nto be me and commit some sort of crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.80,0:23:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely one that, for me, Kudou Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.64,0:23:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would obliterate me personally and socially.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.19,0:23:51.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obliterate you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.44,0:23:54.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he pretended to have lost his memory was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.86,0:24:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to get by without answering any questions\Nput to him by those who might have come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.95,0:24:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the reason he got into the lake without clothes was...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.08,0:24:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the same reason - so he could pretend to have a hoarse voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.12,0:24:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though he could mimic my face...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.91,0:24:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be possible to have my voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.37,0:24:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he couldn't predict what sort of clothes I would be wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.67,0:24:20.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, I fell in that lake as well, when I escaped from the cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.34,0:24:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like I've developed a bit of a hoarse voice myself, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.93,0:24:28.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the one who called the police and an\Nambulance this morning just after the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.89,0:24:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.10,0:24:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd seen him and Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} go into this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.15,0:24:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I then considered what the worst possible outcome would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.40,0:24:39.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, why didn't you go in and stop him?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.82,0:24:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because I couldn't make myself known.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.36,0:24:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he was coming out of the house last night,\NI noticed a bulge on the back of his clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.99,0:24:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was convinced from then that he was carrying a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.12,0:24:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it couldn't be helped, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.96,0:24:56.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the words "Failure means death"\Ncarved onto the desk in that cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.05,0:24:57.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.21,0:25:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was planning to kill a specific person with that gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.01,0:25:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could have tried to stop him, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.22,0:25:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If, at the moment he realized his plan had\Nfailed, he was resolved to kill himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.77,0:25:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would only have a very short interval\Nwhere I could try to prevent that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.19,0:25:16.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I took the bullets from Officer Shiroyama's revolver.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.57,0:25:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And dropped them in front of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.78,0:25:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make him hesitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.07,0:25:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the point when I appeared before him...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.91,0:25:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably when he intended to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.29,0:25:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Okuda...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.12,0:25:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.21,0:25:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hinohara Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.96,0:25:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ma... Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.67,0:25:43.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you really Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.55,0:25:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.84,0:25:48.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It takes time and money to have plastic surgery like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.14,0:25:52.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had money from his\Ninheritance and has been missing for half a year...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.73,0:25:54.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.73,0:25:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.27,0:26:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have concealed the gun inside his own room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.82,0:26:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We brought him here with us, thinking\Nthat would help him recover his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.74,0:26:11.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have retrieved it when he asked us to leave him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.87,0:26:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.46,0:26:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did he have to stab the lady newspaper reporter?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.67,0:26:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thought she'd found him out...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.75,0:26:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When she said that stuff last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.13,0:26:24.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, what's with that face?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.76,0:26:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you think I hadn't found you out?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.72,0:26:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thought she was talking about the\Nplastic surgery to make him into Kudou.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.68,0:26:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I still don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.68,0:26:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This morning when we came running over to this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.56,0:26:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you say that you had stabbed Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.07,0:26:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wanted to pin the crime on Kudou, would\Nit not have been easier to tell us right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.41,0:26:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.66,0:26:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of you guys. As detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.04,0:27:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the circumstances all pointed to this\Nguy, Kudou Shinichi, as the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.42,0:27:04.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to see what kind of deduction you would come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.30,0:27:11.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems we've seen through that quite splendidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.68,0:27:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what happened in the case a year ago!?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.23,0:27:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mayor Hinohara killed his wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.02,0:27:20.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a robbery murder where things were stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.56,0:27:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A stupid deduction that Mayor Hinohara\Ncommitted a forced double suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.61,0:27:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could this guy, Kudou Shinichi, have said that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.16,0:27:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou wasn't wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.16,0:27:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a forced double suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.08,0:27:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit's shoes, the murder weapon, his wife's jewelry...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.38,0:27:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even one of the expensive Niou statues! None of those were there!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.05,0:27:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious that the culprit took those and got away!?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.17,0:27:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.55,0:27:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Mayor Hinohara stabbed his wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.51,0:27:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He collected the murder weapon, the jewelry and\Nthe rest together and sank them in the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.73,0:27:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.27,0:28:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's at least 30 meters from this house to the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.36,0:28:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could he throw them in the lake without leaving any footprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.86,0:28:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just the murder weapon and the jewelry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.24,0:28:12.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ribbons from the medals and the ring\Nfrom the ring toss game were also gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.99,0:28:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ring toss?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.66,0:28:18.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it what Mayor Hinohara's son, Daiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, had said?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.66,0:28:22.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His father was really good at the ring toss, and\Nhe always got a perfect score of 100 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.38,0:28:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The point values as written on the ring toss\Ngame are 10 points, 5 points, and 2 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.47,0:28:32.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think about getting a perfect score of\N100 points, you can't do it without 10 rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.43,0:28:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But here, there are only 9 rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.55,0:28:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And moreover, based on the fact that only\None of the Niou statues was taken...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.10,0:28:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus the fact that Mayor Hinohara was a\Nformer competitor in track and field events...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.90,0:28:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The answer becomes clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.28,0:28:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hammer throw.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.11,0:28:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used the Niou statue as a weight after stuffing the\Nmurder weapon, the shoes, and the jewelry in a sack...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.20,0:29:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he used the ring in the place of a handle, affixing the\Nribbons from the gold medals to it, and then to the bag itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.75,0:29:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to fling it from the veranda to\Nthe lake, similar to the hammer throw.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.09,0:29:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.51,0:29:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he left one of the Niou statues behind was...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.80,0:29:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he'd put both of them in the sack...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.89,0:29:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would become too heavy and wouldn't reach all the way to the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.47,0:29:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.14,0:29:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like that would never make it because of the air resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.06,0:29:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.94,0:29:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bag, the ribbons, and the ring were all recovered from the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.03,0:29:34.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, the wife's blood was found\Non the knife's blade inside the sack.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.20,0:29:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Mayor Hinohara's fingerprints were detected on the handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.16,0:29:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt that Mayor Hinohara\Ncommitted a forced double suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.79,0:29:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It-It's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.92,0:29:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to keep this all from his son, Daiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.84,0:29:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He tried to make it look like a robbery-murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.72,0:29:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.80,0:29:58.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mayor, that generous and good mayor...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.72,0:30:01.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way he'd kill his wife in a forced double suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.52,0:30:04.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, the mayor's cancer was benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.39,0:30:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The claim that he was in despair over learning he had cancer...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.69,0:30:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a downright lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.32,0:30:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he learned he had cancer...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.90,0:30:14.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when it came to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.49,0:30:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A different issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.49,0:30:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mayor Hinohara's blood type...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.20,0:30:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of being examined,\Nhe was told it was actually type-AB.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.71,0:30:27.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.33,0:30:32.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember right, we were told the mayor\Nand his family were a generous type-0 family.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.88,0:30:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.01,0:30:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to Mendel's laws of heredity...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.51,0:30:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A type-AB person and a type-0 cannot give birth to another type-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.35,0:30:41.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.81,0:30:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That meant Daiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} wasn't Mayor Hinohara's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.82,0:30:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.06,0:30:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.94,0:30:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.99,0:31:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.20,0:31:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be bad to tell people that was\Nthe true motive behind the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.00,0:31:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's why the official announcement\Nsaid it was because he learned he had cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.46,0:31:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.75,0:31:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was the case, why didn't anyone tell me!?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.59,0:31:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was a member of the family too!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.88,0:31:19.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.55,0:31:23.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} asked me to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.00,0:31:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must never tell anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.02,0:31:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, please do explain it to Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.61,0:31:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.02,0:31:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was it you told me?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.82,0:31:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The evening after Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} finished\Nhis investigation and left. Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.70,0:31:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, when I think back now...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.45,0:31:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd just been told the truth about Mayor\NHinohara's forced double suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.87,0:31:49.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You might have been too far into shock...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.58,0:31:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And not been paying attention to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.92,0:31:55.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.34,0:31:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.76,0:32:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did I...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.80,0:32:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For what reason? Even my face...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.35,0:32:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it for!?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.22,0:32:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another tragedy caused by unfortunate coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.37,0:32:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing my own face covered in tears right in front of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.90,0:32:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.05,0:32:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would never forget that face.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.21,0:32:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be carved into my heart forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.06,0:32:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that guy, Makoto, was the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.48,0:32:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was the second generation one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.86,0:32:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second generation?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.02,0:32:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first was his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.90,0:33:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After his own daughter died when she got lost in the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.99,0:33:04.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the other children in the village wouldn't suffer the same fate...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.82,0:33:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He built that cabin in the forest and lived there as the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.75,0:33:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, he could frighten people from going into the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.50,0:33:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three years ago, he died from an injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.92,0:33:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that stone by the cabin is...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.67,0:33:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s father's grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.97,0:33:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seem to know an awful lot about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.05,0:33:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I came here a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.31,0:33:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was another problem in addition to the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.35,0:33:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was here to cover the story, and her daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.35,0:33:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had gone into the forest and hadn't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.82,0:33:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard about that from the people at the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.23,0:33:42.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went into the forest to look for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.99,0:33:46.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and just when I was thinking of going in to search myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.62,0:33:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her daughter made it out of the forest on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.62,0:33:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she'd encountered the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} in the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.21,0:33:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she'd run frantically from place to place with him chasing her...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.29,0:33:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before she knew it, she'd come out of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.25,0:34:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to figure that mystery out before\Nthe murder case, so I went into the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.09,0:34:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, I chased after him...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.59,0:34:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I came to that cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.51,0:34:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when I came across Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nin the guise of the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.72,0:34:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.27,0:34:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this time you borrowed the costume\Nfrom where it was left in that cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.31,0:34:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.52,0:34:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My clothes got wet when I fell into\Nthe lake, so that's all I was left with.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.78,0:34:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, looking like this made everyone run away\Nfrom me, so it helped me stay concealed I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.87,0:34:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, I feel sorry for Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.75,0:34:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.29,0:34:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Kawauchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't as badly injured as we thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.54,0:34:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he explains the situation to her later, I think she might forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.46,0:34:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was extremely grateful to the Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}\Nfor rescuing her daughter a year ago, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.98,0:34:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.40,0:34:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong, Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.57,0:35:04.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.99,0:35:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.78,0:35:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit! It's coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.07,0:35:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it's been almost 24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.58,0:35:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got to get Kudou away from them quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.92,0:35:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.67,0:35:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he wanted to ask us some more details about the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.50,0:35:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inspector invited me and Kudou to go see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.51,0:35:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you guys go on to the car ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.18,0:35:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.26,0:35:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.64,0:35:33.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.39,0:35:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I have to ask Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.10,0:35:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a lot of things to ask him!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.40,0:35:40.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.78,0:35:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.28,0:35:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.03,0:35:49.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.49,0:35:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My body...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.78,0:35:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My body's on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.29,0:35:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no, you've got a terrible fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.12,0:35:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, I'll return...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.83,0:36:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll return to being Conan again!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.84,0:36:06.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I turn back now in front of her...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.18,0:36:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a cold! A cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.68,0:36:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember Kudou said he'd fallen into the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.39,0:36:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cold he got then has just come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.14,0:36:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's probably it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.02,0:36:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This much pain is definitely not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.94,0:36:22.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.94,0:36:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying you need to go to the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.90,0:36:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's fine, that's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.28,0:36:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, I'll take Kudou with me to the restroom at the inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.86,0:36:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, can you go get my bag for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.49,0:36:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do I need to bring your bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.62,0:36:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A change of clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.66,0:36:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou's really sweating here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.33,0:36:42.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't have him wearing this Shiragami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} costume forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.33,0:36:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.00,0:36:48.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Twenty four hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.30,0:36:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.93,0:36:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what the professor's little girl said.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.72,0:36:57.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The range of effectiveness of the drug is around 24 hours."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.31,0:37:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Can you please bring Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} back here before that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.77,0:37:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.19,0:37:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if you shrink again, get inside this bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.74,0:37:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll make up some clever story and you can come back out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.41,0:37:17.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.66,0:37:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.91,0:37:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.00,0:37:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you being so sneaky?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.54,0:37:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't come in here, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.21,0:37:27.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the men's restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.84,0:37:30.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, but we're worried about Kudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.19,0:37:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I even asked a doctor who lived nearby to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.63,0:37:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's all fine. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.55,0:37:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just took some cold medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.60,0:37:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of medicine was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.43,0:37:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah well, it was a formula that's been handed down in my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.32,0:37:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.28,0:37:53.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like this every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.07,0:37:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is it always like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.66,0:38:04.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I going to change back without\Nbeing able to tell her anything again?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.25,0:38:09.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I going right back to square one again!?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.10,0:38:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.06,0:38:29.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I turned back.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.57,0:38:32.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi? What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.44,0:38:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, you can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.24,0:38:35.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.37,0:38:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.45,0:38:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gotta hurry and hide in this bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.62,0:38:43.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, I'm calling you!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.50,0:38:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.08,0:38:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran's going to find out my secret identity!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.92,0:38:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.26,0:38:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.38,0:38:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.60,0:39:01.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the next stall...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.93,0:39:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.39,0:39:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.35,0:39:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey now, didn't I already say he was all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.32,0:39:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way he's all right when he's screaming so loud like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.49,0:39:16.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Step aside!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.57,0:39:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.57,0:39:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you can't! Wait, no, you can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.66,0:39:26.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.34,0:39:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K-Kudou?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.01,0:39:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.43,0:39:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you all being so noisy?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.89,0:39:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you be more quiet when I'm on the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.77,0:39:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling better?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.81,0:39:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I feel much better now that that's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.82,0:39:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does seem that your fever's gone down.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.57,0:39:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.86,0:39:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness, I was worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.99,0:40:01.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well now, let's hurry and head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.45,0:40:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you going to tell the detective the details of the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.00,0:40:09.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, I'll do that after we get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.33,0:40:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's good. Just in case, maybe you should go to the hospital too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.21,0:40:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.30,0:40:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.26,0:40:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please excuse us for asking you to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.05,0:40:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.72,0:40:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou! What the hell happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.68,0:40:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'll explain later.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.60,0:40:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.81,0:40:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.81,0:40:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Kudou!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.49,0:40:42.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got him out of trouble somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.41,0:40:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he's got his memory back too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.62,0:40:47.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep, we saved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.12,0:40:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was thanks to your remembering the name\Nof the inn they were staying at, professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.58,0:40:57.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It stood to reason that he'd come running to the\Nrestroom at the inn if he'd gotten cornered like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.05,0:41:04.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.39,0:41:05.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.35,0:41:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no time to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.39,0:41:10.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, swallow this quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.69,0:41:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This, could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.23,0:41:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the prototype antidote for that drug\Nthat turned you into a child, Apotoxin 4869.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.70,0:41:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same drug that you took yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.62,0:41:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I have another 24 hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.66,0:41:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.45,0:41:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taking the same drug frequently makes it lose its effectiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.25,0:41:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your body is building up a resistance to that drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.88,0:41:40.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you continue to take it, its active duration gets shorter.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.42,0:41:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to keep hiding your true identity...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.88,0:41:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get away from those people and return to being...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.89,0:41:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Edogawa Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.74,0:42:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.78,0:42:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing you needed to ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.91,0:42:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing in particular. I just wanted to say thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.33,0:42:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the one who took care of my injuries, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.88,0:42:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Luckily there was a first-aid kit there in that mountain cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.88,0:42:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't see them, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.93,0:42:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, when you were treating my wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.89,0:42:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was wrapping the bandage around your\Nthigh, I did catch a glimpse of something white.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.81,0:42:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did see them! You're the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.77,0:42:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! I didn't look on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.65,0:42:44.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They just happened to come into view.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.53,0:42:45.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.95,0:42:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For letting you see something you didn't want to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.16,0:42:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.37,0:42:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.33,0:42:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to change seats?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.04,0:42:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be easier for you two to talk that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.50,0:42:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK! You stay there, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.67,0:43:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we get home, I'm giving that guy a judo throw.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.96,0:43:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.63,0:43:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. This isn't what I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.68,0:43:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I wanted to ask Shinichi was...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.35,0:43:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I truly need to ask him is...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.11,0:43:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.61,0:43:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that you, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.49,0:43:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Satou and Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.53,0:43:29.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.91,0:43:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just had some business with the Kanagawa prefectural police.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.54,0:43:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since that's over with now, I'm having my Mr. Chauffeur drive me home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.25,0:43:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Chauffeur?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.83,0:43:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.38,0:43:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you have a case or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.92,0:43:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sleeping Kogorou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.46,0:43:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, more-or-less.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.13,0:43:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Well, we're in a hurry to get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.93,0:43:52.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can tell me about the case some other time!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.01,0:43:58.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, with an awesome case like that, even if we\Ndon't tell her, she'll see it in tomorrow's paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.73,0:44:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I think it probably won't be in the newspapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.86,0:44:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, nobody died.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.03,0:44:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the culprit is still a minor...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.32,0:44:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they can't reveal his name or show a photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.03,0:44:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as for the lady newspaper reporter who was stabbed...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.62,0:44:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems she's not going to write about it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.04,0:44:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lucky, weren't you, Kudou?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.96,0:44:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that car?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.59,0:44:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They keep scraping the side of their car against the guardrail.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.06,0:44:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they fell asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.64,0:44:40.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they keep it up, there's gonna be a bad accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.15,0:44:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.24,0:44:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.54,0:45:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! There's something strange about the way he looks!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.04,0:45:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get the car out in front of his!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.17,0:45:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, "in front"? You're not saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.68,0:45:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that we're in front, lower your speed bit by bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.30,0:45:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! I can't do that with a rental car!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.06,0:45:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just do it! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.00,0:45:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Gunpei! Gunpei!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.29,0:45:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait! Don't touch him!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.29,0:45:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please step back.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.71,0:45:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.05,0:45:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.05,0:45:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's no longer breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.47,0:45:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, Kudou.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.18,0:45:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's been hemorrhaging in his eyelids.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.97,0:46:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.77,0:46:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Line marks!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.27,0:46:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudou, this guy was...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.48,0:46:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.07,0:46:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.57,0:46:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, there's a tollbooth one kilometer ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.53,0:46:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call Detective Satou and ask her to setup a blockade there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.83,0:46:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.70,0:46:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's dead. The driver of this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.25,0:46:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been strangled.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.67,0:46:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strangled?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.00,0:46:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, while he was driving...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.34,0:46:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside the closed environment of this car.
